article.description: Quinton Chievous and Brian Darden scored 19 points apiece to lead Hampton to a 75-64 win over Louisiana-Monroe in the Continental Tires Las Vegas Classic on Wednesday.
article.headline: Hampton defeats Louisiana-Monroe 75-64 in Las Vegas
article.linkText: Hampton defeats Louisiana-Monroe 75-64 in Las Vegas
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Quinton Chievous and Brian Darden scored 19 points apiece to lead Hampton to a 75-64 win over Louisiana-Monroe in the Continental Tires Las Vegas Classic on Wednesday. Reginald Johnson added 16 for the Pirates (5-6), who led 42-30 at the half and stretch that to 16 early in the second. They did it by controlling the inside with a 40-33 rebound advantage for a 44-26 difference on points in the paint. Chievous and Dionte Adams both had eight rebounds. Majok Deng had 16 points for the Warhawks (5-7) with Justin Roberson and Nick Coppola adding 12. Hampton led by a dozen barely five minutes into the game after a Darden 3-pointer capped a 10-0 in which Darden scored the last eight points. Darden had 13 points at halftime, hitting three 3s. Chievous had 10 points in the second half, missing only one of six shots.
